Class SeqIter

java.lang.Object
com.pld.agile.model.algorithm.tsp.SeqIter
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterator<Integer>
public class SeqIter extends Object implements Iterator<Integer>
The SeqIter class implements an Iterator for traversing the set of unvisited vertices that are successors of a given current vertex in a graph. The vertices are traversed in the same order as they appear in the unvisited set.

    • SeqIter

      public SeqIter(Collection<Integer> unvisited, int currentVertex, Graph g)
      Creates an iterator to traverse the set of vertices in unvisited that are successors of currentVertex in the graph g. Vertices are traversed in the same order as in unvisited.
      Parameters:
      unvisited - the set of unvisited vertices
      currentVertex - the current vertex from which successors are considered
      g - the Graph object representing the graph
